\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 And so, after that day, Eddie had left the apothecary.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 For the first time in so many years, Eddie excused himself from his parents, Markus and everyone at the apothecary that Eddie will be taking a break from the potion mixing to study Alchemy, everyone at the apothecary rechieved it well.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Since then, for everyday he would wake up early, tidy up his bedroom and took his sister to school now that he had time to do that. He would board the ferry into Osthaven with her, but it wasn\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92t just for Torrie, what Eddie was looking for was the library in it.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 The library was located not far from the Sage Institute building, but it is still a library curated by the Sage\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s Institute. It wasn\u8217\'92t such a big library, but it houses enough books for Eddie to study on.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 And so Eddie sat down for the entire day, books mounting on his pile on and on as he continued reading, notebooks filled with notes upon notes from different books as he studied a theory and find a book to challenge the previous one. }
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 And when the day was over, he went back to Aella Academy, talked to Mr. Ferie about what he had learned and took Torrie home.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 And thus was his new routine, for days.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Days has gone into weeks}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Exam is approaching.}
